        return False
```

This solution uses dynamic programming to determine the length of the longest palindromic subsequence in the string `s`. The 2D array `f` is used to store the lengths of the longest palindromic subsequences for different substrings of `s`. The main idea is to check if the length of the longest palindromic subsequence plus `k` is at least the length of the string `s`. If it is, then it means that by removing at most `k` characters, the string can be transformed into a palindrome.
